# Parallel Agent Orchestration

- For multi-agent execution, follow `docs/runbooks/parallel-agent-delivery-model.md`.
- Send orchestration prompts in chat only. Do not create prompt documents in `docs/`.
- Agents should infer their role from chat context, then read their role doc in `docs/guides/roles/`.
- Every work package must include explicit file ownership boundaries and non-overlap constraints.
- Every work package must update `docs/specs/goal-<n>-progress.md` before it is considered complete.
- Use the standard response template from the runbook for all role handoffs.
- Architect may apply small, low-risk quick fixes during review; larger changes must be delegated as explicit work packages.

